				<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The legal team at The Walker Firm is fully committed to getting positive results. We express our dedication through our hard work, keen attention to detail and ongoing dialogue with our clients. We are passionate about fighting for your rights and giving you the legal representation you deserve. Give us a call today to discuss matters with a team of attorneys you can rely on.</p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">Frequently Asked Questions About A DUI </h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Q: What should I do after I am released from jail after a DUI? </strong></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A:</strong> Be sure to write down the events of your arrests, who was in the car with you, weather conditions, where were you going, etc... </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Q: Can I represent myself in my DUI case? </strong></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A:</strong> Yes, but without being familiar with the legal process, it is not advised. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Q: What can I do to help prepare for my legal defense? </strong></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A: </strong>Getting a head start on community service and enrolling in a drunk driving program are good things to do before your case is presented. Keeping all your documents regarding your case all in one place. Be sure to share all information about your case with your attorney, no matter how irrelevant the information may seem. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">If you have been charged with a DUI, this can lead to serious legal consequences. In some cases, your license may be immediately revoked. The implications of a DUI are not to be downplayed. Get legal representation from an attorney that stands up for your rights. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Many drivers who are charged with a DUI are unfamiliar with the rights they hold in such a situation. Our professional team is prepared to help resolve any concerns you may have, offering reliable guidance to help you sort out the charges and obtain an ideal result. When you call us, we will be at your side in the blink of an eye. Call our Warner Robins, GA office at <a href=\"tel: (478) 923-4152\" data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">(478) 923-4152</a> to speak with our DUI lawyer.</p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">Understanding DUI Under Georgia Law</h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The following article will cover: </strong></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The definition of DUI under Georgia Law, including alcohol, drugs, and toxic substances. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">DUI with Aggravating Factors in Georgia, such as age, controlled substances, collisions, and prior offenses. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The consequences that come after DUI arrests, and the importance of hiring a DUI attorney. </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<img src=\"https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-8.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-8.jpg 300w, https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-8-150x150.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" alt=\"Understanding DUI Under Georgia Law\" class=\"wp-image-5163 img-fluid float-end\">\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">What Is The Definition Of DUI Under Georgia Law? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Under Georgia law, a DUI (Driving Under the Influence) is defined under Georgia Code section 40-6-391. The law states that a person is considered to be driving under the influence if they are in actual physical control of a moving vehicle while under the influence of any substance that impairs their ability to drive safely. This includes: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being under the influence of alcohol to the extent that it is less safe for the person to drive. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being under the influence of any drug to the extent that it is less safe for the person to drive. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being under the intentional influence of any glue, aerosol, or other toxic vapor to the extent that it is less safe for the person to drive. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being under the combined influence of any two or more substances specified in paragraphs 1-3, to the extent that it is less safe for the person to drive. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Having an alcohol concentration of 0.08 grams or more at any time within three hours after driving or being in actual physical control, due to alcohol consumed before such driving or being in actual physical control ended. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Having any amount of marijuana or controlled substances, as defined in code section 16-13-21, present in the person\'s blood or urine, or both, including the metabolites and derivatives of each or both, regardless of the presence of any alcohol in the person\'s breath or blood. </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">This is a comprehensive outline of the six subsections that define a DUI under Georgia law. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">What Is A DUI With Aggravating Factors In Georgia? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">In Georgia, a DUI charge can be compounded with aggravating factors. These are specific conditions that, if present during the DUI incident, can elevate the seriousness of the offense. The following are examples of aggravating factors: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant is under the age of 21. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">There is a presence of non-prescribed controlled substances detected in the toxicology. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A child was present in the vehicle during the incident. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant caused a collision with another vehicle. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant hit another vehicle that was occupied. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant was driving a commercial vehicle while under the influence. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant\'s blood alcohol level was over 0.15 or 0.20 grams. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">There was another suspendable traffic offense committed concurrently with the DUI. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant had a prior DUI within five years of the current citation or arrest date. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The defendant had an additional DUI within ten years of the current pending DUI citation or arrest. </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">These are just examples of what could constitute as aggravating factors under Georgia law. Each case may have unique circumstances that could influence the final judgment. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">What Happens After I Am Formally Arrested For DUI? Will I Be Taken To Jail Right After The DUI Arrest In Georgia? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Once you are placed under formal arrest for DUI, the law enforcement officer - be it an officer, trooper, or deputy - is obliged to read you the Georgia Implied Consent card. This card outlines your rights and requests your consent to submit to a state-administered test of your blood or urine. This reading is conducted after the arrest but before leaving the arrest scene. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Following this, the officer will ensure your vehicle is secured. This may involve waiting for a tow truck, releasing the vehicle to another deputy, or allowing a friend or family member to take the vehicle. Once the vehicle is dealt with, you will be transported to the county or city jail for booking procedures. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">What Happens To My Driver\'s License After A DUI Or OUI Arrest? Can Hiring A DUI Attorney Help To Protect My Driver\'s License? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The status of your driver\'s license post-arrest largely depends on the circumstances surrounding your case. If you refused the state-administered test, it is crucial to consult a DUI lawyer within 30 days of your DUI arrest. The reason for this urgency is that your license could be subject to a 12-month suspension if you don\'t take certain actions within this timeline. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">However, it\'s essential to note that your license is not automatically suspended upon a DUI arrest. If you\'ve been issued DDS form 1205 and do not request a hearing, fail to appeal, or neglect to install an interlock device in your vehicle, your license will be suspended on the 46th day after the DUI for 12 months. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">This suspension can occur if your Blood Alcohol Concentration (BAC) level is 0.08 grams or higher. However, if you submitted to the state-administered test and possess a regular full driver\'s license, your license typically does not get suspended immediately after a DUI arrest. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Remember, contacting an attorney as soon as possible after your arrest can be critical in navigating the legal complexities surrounding a DUI charge, especially when your driving privileges are at stake. For more information on the Definition Of DUI Under Georgia Law, an <a href=\"/contact-us/\" data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">initial consultation</a> is your next best step. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">More Information</h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><a href=\"/aftermath-of-a-dui-arrest-in-georgia/\" data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The Aftermath Of A DUI Arrest In Georgia</a><br data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n					</div>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n\n	<script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Is The Definition Of DUI Under Georgia Law?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Under Georgia law, a DUI (Driving Under the Influence) is defined under Georgia Code section 40-6-391. The law states that a person is considered to be driving under the influence if they are in actual physical control of a moving vehicle while under the influence of any substance that impairs their ability to drive safely. \"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Is A DUI With Aggravating Factors In Georgia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In Georgia, a DUI charge can be compounded with aggravating factors. These are specific conditions that, if present during the DUI incident, can elevate the seriousness of the offense.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Happens After I Am Formally Arrested For DUI? Will I Be Taken To Jail Right After The DUI Arrest In Georgia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Once you are placed under formal arrest for DUI, the law enforcement officer - be it an officer, trooper, or deputy - is obliged to read you the Georgia Implied Consent card. This card outlines your rights and requests your consent to submit to a state-administered test of your blood or urine. This reading is conducted after the arrest but before leaving the arrest scene.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Happens To My Driver\'s License After A DUI Or OUI Arrest? Can Hiring A DUI Attorney Help To Protect My Driver\'s License?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The status of your driver\'s license post-arrest largely depends on the circumstances surrounding your case. If you refused the state-administered test, it is crucial to consult a DUI lawyer within 30 days of your DUI arrest. The reason for this urgency is that your license could be subject to a 12-month suspension if you don\'t take certain actions within this timeline.\"}}]}</script><!--FAQPage Code Generated by https://saijogeorge.com/json-ld-schema-generator/faq/-->\n</section>\n\n<section>\n	<div lc-helper=\"shortcode\" class=\"live-shortcode\">[lc_get_post post_type=\"lc_section\" slug=\"johnsonbox\"]</div>\n</section>\n','DUI Law Attorneys','','publish','closed','closed','','dui','','','2023-06-26 05:44:23','2023-06-26 05:44:23','',0,'https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/?page_id=5123',0,'page','',0),(5124,1,'2023-06-23 04:47:37','2023-06-23 04:47:37','\n<section>\n	<div class=\"container\">\n		<div class=\"row\">\n			<div class=\"col-md-12\">\n				<div class=\"lc-block\">\n					<div editable=\"rich\">\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">Benefiting From Our Lawyers </h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">If you have received a traffic violation in can have a bigger impact than you would expect. Your insurance rates can go up and your driving record could be tarnished. When you have received a traffic ticket, you want to work with an attorney that is experienced and can be trusted. The professionals at The Walker Firm is the only call you will need to make. Give us a call today for your free initial consultation to see how we can help! </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">In matters of traffic law, you may have been unjustly accused of speeding, running a red light or being over-ticketed for a minor infraction. We have worked with many clients over the years and understand the nuances and complications involved with traffic law cases. Let our experienced and hard working team get to the bottom of your case. We’ll help you obtain a fair and just result.</p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">Traffic Law Legal Services For Individuals In The Middle Georgia Area</h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">We can help with a variety of traffic offenses including: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">No License or Suspended License </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Speeding Tickets </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Running a Red Light/Stop Sign </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being pulled over w/o Insurance </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Reckless Driving </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Hit &amp; Run </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"> </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\