ac-font-size=\"22\">What Are The Most Common Serious Traffic Offenses Charged In Georgia? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Serious traffic offenses in Georgia are dominated by the following offenses: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Driving under the Influence (DUI) </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Driving with a suspended license </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Operating a vehicle without insurance </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Driving a vehicle with a suspended, canceled, or revoked registration </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">These are among the most frequent serious violations that are encountered. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">When Does A Traffic Violation Become A Misdemeanor Or Another More Serious Offense? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A traffic violation can escalate to a felony under certain circumstances. This may occur if a person, previously declared a habitual violator, is caught driving a vehicle or receives a DUI. Other scenarios include serious injury or vehicular homicide resulting from a traffic accident. </p>\n						<h4>What Scenarios Most Commonly Lead To A Suspended License? And Can You Help With The Suspended License? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The most common reasons leading to license suspension include: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Failing to appear in traffic court </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Failing to pay a fine within the designated time frame </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Being charged with a DUI </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Not paying child support </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">While I can provide assistance if you\'ve been charged with driving with a suspended license, please note that in the case of a DUI-related suspension, the duration of the suspension is determined by the state of Georgia and cannot be shortened. </p>\n						<h4 data-spkac-font-size=\"22\">Should I Just Pay My Traffic Offense Fine And Be Done With It, Or Do I Really Need A Georgia Traffic Offense Attorney? </h4>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The decision to hire a Georgia Traffic Offense Attorney largely depends on your specific circumstances. For instance, a Commercial Driver’s License (CDL) holder may have a greater incentive to contest a traffic citation. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Bear in mind that paying a traffic citation equates to an admission of guilt. It could potentially impact you adversely in civil proceedings related to a traffic accident. Furthermore, paying a citation may lead to a significant increase in your insurance premiums. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Therefore, while it is not mandatory to hire an attorney for every traffic citation, it would be wise to consider the specific facts and potential consequences of your situation before deciding. For more information on Traffic Offenses In Georgia, an <a href=\"/contact-us/\" data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">initial consultation</a> is your next best step</p>\n					</div>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n\n	<script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Are The Most Common Serious Traffic Offenses Charged In Georgia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Serious traffic offenses in Georgia are dominated by the following offenses:\\n\\nDriving under the Influence (DUI)\\nDriving with a suspended license\\nOperating a vehicle without insurance\\nDriving a vehicle with a suspended, canceled, or revoked registration\\nThese 