ille, GA<br></li>\n							<li>Dry Branch, GA<br></li>\n							<li>Clinchfield, GA<br></li>\n							<li>Bonaire, GA<br></li>\n							<li>Byron, GA<br></li>\n							<li>Macon, GA <br></li>\n						</ul>\n						<p></p>\n					</div>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n</section>\n','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4773-autosave-v1','','','2023-06-23 11:00:00','2023-06-23 11:00:00','',4773,'https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/?p=5154',0,'revision','',0),(5155,1,'2023-06-23 12:03:30','2023-06-23 12:03:30','\n<section>\n	<div class=\"container\">\n		<div class=\"row\">\n			<div class=\"col-md-12\">\n				<div class=\"lc-block\">\n					<div editable=\"rich\">\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"><strong data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The following article will cover: </strong></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Procedures used during a DUI arrest, including the request for a blood test and potential consequences of refusing. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Jail time and penalties for DUI convictions in Georgia, with varying durations based on aggravating factors and prior offenses. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The importance of hiring a DUI attorney to navigate the legal complexities and protect rights – even if you are considering a guilty plea. </li>\n						</ul>\n						<img src=\"https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-14.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-14.jpg 300w, https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-14-150x150.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" alt=\"The Aftermath Of A DUI Arrest In Georgia\" class=\"wp-image-5164 img-fluid float-end\">\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">What Happens At The Station During A DUI Arrest? Do I Have To Take A Breathalyzer? What Happens If I Refuse? </h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Following recent decisions from the Georgia Supreme Court and Court of Appeals, the arresting officer will typically request a blood test. This request is often made at the scene, after reading the implied consent law. This law asks for your agreement to undergo a blood test at the police station. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">If you refuse this blood test, typically, two things may happen: </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<ul data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The officer might seek a search warrant from a judge based on probable cause, to legally obtain your blood for chemical testing. </li>\n							<li data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">The officer may choose not to seek a warrant. In such scenarios, you may be issued a DDS form 1205, which has strict time limitations. </li>\n						</ul>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\"></p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">While you have the right to refuse any chemical testing under Georgia law, be aware that such refusal can lead to enhanced consequences. These might include receiving DDS form 1205, which could lead to a license suspension under the Administrative License Suspension (ALS) process. </p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">Am I Going To Jail For A DUI Conviction In Georgia? And What Are The Penalties For DUI Conviction? </h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Georgia law mandates jail time even for first-time <a href=\"/dui/\">DUI </a>offenders. The minimum jail time is 24 hours. Depending on the presence of aggravating factors, this period can increase. Multiple aggravating factors can lead to considerably longer jail time, potentially 30 or 60 days, even for a first-time DUI. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">For a second DUI within 10 years, the minimum jail time increases to 72 hours, and penalties escalate with each subsequent offense. For instance, a third DUI within 10 years results in a minimum jail time of 15 days. </p>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">A person who receives three DUIs within five years will be declared a habitual violator. Any subsequent DUI during this period of habitual violator status escalates the offense to a felony. The minimum sentence for a felony DUI under Georgia law is one year, although certain circumstances can lead to shorter sentences. </p>\n						<h3 data-spkac-font-size=\"35\">If I Plead Guilty To DUI, Do I Still Need To Hire A DUI Attorney Or Can I Handle My DUI Case On My Own? </h3>\n						<p data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">Pleading guilty essentially concludes your case and forfeits many rights to appeal or change your plea. Despite this, it is strongly recommended that anyone facing a DUI charge seek the counsel of a qualified DUI attorney. An attorney can provide invaluable insights into the nuances of DUI laws and potential defenses that an average person may not be aware of. Given the serious consequences, including jail time and license suspensions, hiring a DUI attorney is a wise step to protect your rights and navigate the complexities of a DUI case. For more information on the Aftermath Of A DUI Arrest In Georgia, an <a href=\"/contact-us/\" data-spkac-font-size=\"16\">initial consultation</a> is your next best step.</p>\n					</div>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n\n	<script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What Happens At The Station During A DUI Arrest? Do I Have To Take A Breathalyzer? What Happens If I Refuse?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Following recent decisions from the Georgia Supreme Court and Court of Appeals, the arresting officer will typically request a blood test. This request is often made at the scene, after reading the implied consent law. This law asks for your agreement to undergo a blood test at the police station.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Am I Going To Jail For A DUI Conviction In Georgia? And What Are The Penalties For DUI Conviction?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Georgia law mandates jail time even for first-time DUI offenders. The minimum jail time is 24 hours. Depending on the presence of aggravating factors, this period can increase. Multiple aggravating factors can lead to considerably longer jail time, potentially 30 or 60 days, even for a first-time DUI.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"If I Plead Guilty To DUI, Do I Still Need To Hire A DUI Attorney Or Can I Handle My DUI Case On My Own?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Pleading guilty essentially concludes your case and forfeits many rights to appeal or change your plea. Despite this, it is strongly recommended that anyone facing a DUI charge seek the counsel of a qualified DUI attorney. An attorney can provide invaluable insights into the nuances of DUI laws and potential defenses that an average person may not be aware of. Given the serious consequences, including jail time and license suspensions, hiring a DUI attorney is a wise step to protect your rights and navigate the complexities of a DUI case. For more information on the Aftermath Of A DUI Arrest In Georgia, an initial consultation is your next best step.\"}}]}</script><!--FAQPage Code Generated by https://saijogeorge.com/json-ld-schema-generator/faq/-->\n</section>\n<section>\n	<div lc-helper=\"shortcode\" class=\"live-shortcode\">[lc_get_post post_type=\"lc_section\" slug=\"johnsonbox\"]</div>\n</section>\n','The Aftermath Of A DUI Arrest In Georgia','','publish','closed','closed','','aftermath-of-a-dui-arrest-in-georgia','','','2023-06-26 05:57:26','2023-06-26 05:57:26','',0,'https://thewalkerfirm.wpengine.com/?page_id=5155',0,'page','',0),(5156,1,'2023-06-23 12:34:11','2023-06-23 12:34:11','','Jay-Walker','','inherit','open','cl